article.headline: IUPUI 64, W. Illinois 47
article.story: MACOMB, Ill. (AP) -- Forward Billy Pettiford scored a game-high 16 points and George Hill added 15 as IUPUI defeated Western Illinois 64-47 on Saturday night. Austin Montgomery added 13 points and Jon Avery came off the bench to score 10 for the Jaguars (6-2, 1-0 Summit). IUPUI went into halftime with a 31-26 lead. The Leathernecks (3-6, 0-1 Summit) had just two players in double digits. Forward Jerryck Owens-Murrey scored 14 points, and James Washington chipped in 13. Western Illinois shot poorly from the field, making just 25 percent (6-of-24) in the second half. That compared with IUPUI's 50 percent (9-of-18) after halftime.
